`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The codebase pattern for R3F component testing is:
1. Export pure math functions (no Three.js imports) that can be unit-tested without WebGL
2. Mock `@react-three/drei`, `@react-three/fiber`, and `three` at the top of test files
3. Use imperative refs (`materialRef.current.opacity = value`) in `useFrame` to avoid React state per frame — only use `useState` for structural changes (entity count changes)
